abstract = {The prospect of a metaverse has fascinated the imagination of technologists, futurists, and urbanists alike, with its potential to fundamentally alter the daily experiences of life, work, recreation, and interaction in the city. This chapter will delve comprehensively into the concept of the metaverse, tracing its history from the earliest musings on VR to its current form as a rapidly evolving technology. The chapter will survey the challenges that must be overcome to realize the full potential of the metaverse, including issues related to standardization, privacy and security, and the limited practical applications. The foundation for growth of the metaverse is also keenly explored, including the growth in computing power, the emergence of robust networks, and the increasing prevalence of decentralized systems. The chapter then turns to the applications of the metaverse in the realm of smart cities, including its potential for innovative urban planning and design, the ability to offer remote access to services and experiences, and its role in catalyzing public engagement. Ultimately, the chapter argues that the metaverse holds great promise for the future of cities and urban life and has the potential to be a transformative force in the development of smart cities.}
