abstract = {It is well-known that the deployment of Internet-connected devices is increasing in houses, but these devices are subject to numerous threats from both privacy and security aspects. An authentic entity (for example, the device builder) may be collecting data about the user without the user's knowledge. In this chapter, we have highlighted several of the security aspects of smart homes and the Power Internet of Things (PIoT). Next, we propose the Secure IoT structural design for smart cities as a whole, which is applicable to smart homes and the Power Internet of Things (PIoT). In general, a security framework designed for the Power Internet of Things (PIoT) is comprised of three layers, including the perception layer, network layer, and application layer. We have highlighted attacks on these layers. Next, we propose our model for the security of the PIoT. Next, we highlight our Hybrid RSA cipher approach and how its lightweight, efficient architecture can be incorporated into the future Internet of Things (IoT) and the Internet of Everything (IoE). Finally, we present several real-time performance evaluations that defend our claims.}
